      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies and a soaring 8,000 RPM redline. This example maintains its mechanical integrity with a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential providing excellent torque vectoring. The chassis remains composed through high-lateral-G maneuvers thanks to well-sorted suspension geometry, and the rear subframe has been proactively inspected for structural rigidity. While showing honest signs of road use consistent with its age, the high-revving induction note and tactile steering feedback remain uncompromised. Recent service includes a comprehensive VANOS system refresh and a precise valve adjustment to ensure peak volumetric efficiency. This is a mechanically sound enthusiast's tool ready for the tarmac.",
